"2017/11/09 5:44:18 PM UTC+1","Practical considerations in 3D magnetic resonance force microscopy",Poster,"Magnetic resonance force microscopy (MRFM) is a technique that reconstructs the 3D density distribution of nuclear spin species in nanoscale samples, such as individual macromolecules. While the feasibility of the method has been demonstrated \cite{1}, state-of-the-art experiments have not yet reached the subnanometer regime required to reveal detailed molecular structures.

