7 Oe at 6.5 GHz. Further investigation was done using time and spatially resolved Kerr microscopy. Here we see various standing spin waves including Damon Eshbach Modes and Backward Volume Modes. Based on these measurements also the damping for a single resonator could be determined to $\alpha < 4\times 10^{-4}$. The modes observed can be nicely reproduced in 3D micromagnetic simulations.","[1] https://doi.org/doi:10.1038/nature08967
